definitions.definition: To assemble from thin sheets glued together to make a thicker sheet.
examples: We'll laminate the piece of wood with grain going in different directions to make a really strong hull for the boat.

definitions.definition: To cover (something flat, usually paper) in adhesive protective plastic.
examples: We laminated the printouts so we could use them as signage.

definitions.definition: To form (metal etc.) into a thin plate, as by rolling.
To cause to separate into thin plates or layers; to divide into thin plates.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To assemble from thin sheets glued together to make a thicker sheet.
